    <scopecontent id="scope">
	
<p>	The collection contains documents pertaining to Elihu Grant's professional and personal life while working at Smith and after including correspondence to his family, especially to his wife Almy Chase Grant and some correspondence to Mrs. Grant from others, including Grace Coolidge. The collection also includes photographs of the family, Grant's publications while working at Smith, sound recordings of his lectures, his obituaries and biographies, and a memorabilia album that documents the Grant's marriage as well as small notes marking the anniversary of their marriage.</p>
    </scopecontent>

